The following formula is a generalization of $(1)$
\begin{align}
\small\int_{-\infty}^\infty\frac{dx}{\left(e^x+e^{-x}+e^{a+ix\sqrt{3}}\right)^2}+e^a\int_{-\infty}^\infty\frac{dx}{\left(e^{a+x}+e^{-x}+e^{ix\sqrt{3}}\right)^2}+e^a\int_{-\infty}^\infty\frac{dx}{\left(e^{a+x}+e^{-x}+e^{-ix\sqrt{3}}\right)^2}=1
\end{align}
where $|a|$ is sufficiently small. It gives a parametric extension of $(1)$. I think it is hard to expect anything more simple than this.
